Class HumanNPC

java.lang.Object

Human, Intractable
public class HumanNPC extends Object implements Intractable, Human
Allows to create SIMPLE player NPCs with support of clicks. For complex NPCs use CitizensAPI TODO -> Rework NMS using protocol maybe?

      public HumanNPC(org.bukkit.Location location, @Nullable String npcName, @Nullable String skinOwner)
      Create instance of HumanNPC class.
      Parameters:
      location - - Location of NPC.
      npcName - - Name of NPC. Null will convert NPC's name to "&e&lCLICK". Keep blank string to remove name.
      skinOwner - - Skin owner. Leave empty or null to apply skin later. Only use online players names for this. See setSkinAsync(String) disclaimer.

      public void setSkinSync(String skinOwner)

    • setSkinAsync

      public void setSkinAsync(String skinOwner)
      Warning, please read before using. This method grabs texture from Mojang API asynchronously, which will result in delay. After textures will be applied, NPC will reload, resetting all per-player packet changes applied before this. I recommend use setSkin(String, String) to apply textures and signature manually, instead of grabbing it from API. You can use https://mineskin.org/gallery to grab textures and signature for skins that are permanent. Grabbing skin from players name also means that skin is not permanent and will change upon players changing it.
      Parameters:
      skinOwner - - Name (nick) of minecraft account.
